  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the best YouTube channels for UPSC preparation besides all materials?",
  "response": "For UPSC preparation, YouTube channels can be a great supplement to study materials, as they offer video lectures, analysis, current affairs updates, and strategy sessions. Here are some of the best YouTube channels for UPSC aspirants:\n\n---\n\n### **General Studies and Comprehensive Preparation**\n1. **Unacademy IAS (formerly known as Let's Crack UPSC CSE)**  \n   - Offers free and paid courses, live classes, and daily current affairs updates.  \n   - Highly experienced educators like Roman Saini, Atish Mathur, and more.\n\n2. **Study IQ IAS**  \n   - Known for comprehensive coverage of UPSC syllabus, current affairs, and optional subjects.  \n   - Dr. Gaurav Garg and team provide detailed lectures.\n\n3. **Vision IAS**  \n   - Focuses on current affairs, strategy, and quality content for UPSC preparation.  \n   - Highly recommended for their ethics and essay videos.\n\n4. **Drishti IAS**  \n   - Provides daily current affairs (in Hindi and English), mock tests, and subject-wise lectures.  \n   - Great for Hindi medium aspirants.\n\n5. **OnlyIAS (formerly known as Praveen Mishra IAS)**  \n   - Known for simplified explanations and holistic coverage of the UPSC syllabus.\n\n---\n\n### **Current Affairs and News Analysis**\n6. **The Hindu Analysis by Study IQ**  \n   - Daily newspaper analysis, focusing on The Hindu, which is crucial for UPSC.\n\n7. **Lukmaan IAS**  \n   - Provides daily current affairs updates and in-depth analysis of important topics.\n\n8. **Next IAS**  \n   - Offers daily current affairs videos, editorial analysis, and topic-wise explanations.\n\n---\n\n### **Specific Subjects and Optional Preparation**\n9. **Pritam Singh (Geography)**  \n   - Focuses on geography, a key subject for UPSC.\n\n10. **Rajtanil Solanki (History and Art & Culture)**  \n    - Known for detailed lectures on history and culture.\n\n11. **M Puri Sir (for Polity and Governance)**  \n    - Specializes in Indian polity, making complex topics easy to understand.\n\n---\n\n### **Essay and Ethics Preparation**\n12. **Magnet Brains (Essay Writing)**  \n    - Offers strategies and examples for essay writing in UPSC.\n\n13. **Sleepy Classes (Ethics, Essay, and Optional Subjects)**  \n    - Known for their unique and engaging teaching style for ethics and essay.\n\n---\n\n### **Mock Tests and Answer Writing**\n14. **UPSC Pathshala**  \n    - Focuses on answer writing practice and mock tests.\n\n15. **Civilsdaily**  \n    - Offers daily current affairs, practice questions, and answer writing tips.\n\n---\n\n### **Motivation and Strategy**\n16. **Mrunal Patel**  \n    - Known for his economic and budget analysis, as well as UPSC strategy videos.\n\n17. **Shashank Sajwan (AIR 98, UPSC 2021)**  \n    - Shares his journey, tips, and strategies for UPSC aspirants.\n\n18. **Apoorvanand (Motivation and Strategy)**  \n    - Provides motivational content and guidance for UPSC preparation.\n\n---\n\n### **Hindi Medium Aspirants**\n19. **Aaj Tak UPSC**  \n    - Focuses on current affairs and news analysis in Hindi.\n\n20. **Ravi Sihag**  \n    - Offers comprehensive lectures in Hindi for all UPSC subjects.\n\n---\n\nThese channels, combined with your standard study materials, can help you stay updated, understand complex topics, and improve your preparation strategy. Always focus on quality over quantity and choose channels that best suit your needs.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
